{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/making-your-ubuntu-deep-learning-ready-a710cb337b39", "time": 1683010005.573389, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/making-your-ubuntu-deep-learning-ready-a710cb337b39/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Making your Ubuntu deep learning ready | by Kantajit Shaw | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Making your Ubuntu deep learning ready", "description": "I have stumbled upon many guides to install deep learning libraries, Cuda, cuDNN & nvidia-driver. But I have never been successful in one go following only one guide. So, I decided to write this\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-gpus#compute", "anchor_text": "link", "paragraph_index": 2}, {"url": "https://docs.nvidia.com/deploy/cuda-compatibility/index.html#binary-compatibility__table-toolkit-driver", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 6}, {"url": "https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-toolkit-archive", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 8}, {"url": "https://www.tensorflow.org/install/source#gpu", "anchor_text": "table", "paragraph_index": 9}, {"url": "https://developer.nvidia.com/rdp/cudnn-archive", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 9}, {"url": "https://pytorch.org/get-started/locally/", "anchor_text": "link", "paragraph_index": 11}], "all_paragraphs": ["I have stumbled upon many guides to install deep learning libraries, Cuda, cuDNN & nvidia-driver. But I have never been successful in one go following only one guide. So, I decided to write this article. First, this guide is to install deep learning libraries ( TensorFlow, Keras, PyTorch) with GPU support. CPU support is pretty straight-forward, so I won\u2019t be talking about that.", "NVIDIA\u00ae GPU card with CUDA\u00ae Compute Capability 3.5 or higher.", "You can check whether your GPU is compatible or not by visiting this link.", "Run these following commands. It adds the necessary repository to download the Nvidia driver. It will", "It will show you the driver versions compatible with your GPU card. I have an RTX 2060 super GPU card. It shows", "It may also show multiple entries depending on the GPU card you are using. Example", "Install the suitable version. Your driver will decide the minimum version of CUDA you are going to install. You can find the table here.", "Repace xxx with your desired version. Reboot and check the installation", "Download the CUDA installer from here. I prefer installing from the runfile. Install and then add the paths in PATH and LD_LIBRARY_PATH variable. Replace the path of Cuda (in my case /usr/local/cuda-10.1/ ) with your path.", "Visit this table get the tested build versions. Check the version of cuDNN you need to install. Download the cuDNN from here. I prefer the zipped version.", "After downloading unzip and copy the files to CUDA directory.", "To install PyTorch with GPU support visit this link. Select Version, OS, Language, package installer, CUDA version and then follow the highlighted portion of the following image to install.", "There you have it. Now verify your installation using these python scripts.", "All the libraries are installed. Now turn your CREATIVE mode on.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Deep learning enthusiast, interested in Computer Vision and Natural Language Processing problems."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Fa710cb337b39&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fmaking-your-ubuntu-deep-learning-ready-a710cb337b39&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatasc